      <p>
        The word 'shorshe' means mustard and 'ilish' refers to hilsa fish.
        Shorshe Ilish is a popular Bengali dish made with hilsa fish and a mustard-based gravy.
        Shorshe Ilish has been a part of Bengali cuisine for centuries and is considered to be a quintessential Bengali dish. 
        It is often served during important occasions such as weddings, festivals, and other celebrations.
    </p>

